# DynamicTable

Use the shared `DynamicTable` for feature lists. Do not invent a parallel DataTable or bury row actions inside `ColumnConfig.format`.

## Layout

| Concern | Path |
|---------|------|
| Table | `src/components/shared/table/dynamic-table.tsx` |
| Feature columns | `src/features/<feature>/components/tables/*-table-columns.tsx` |
| List pages | `src/features/<feature>/components/pages/*list-page-component.tsx` |

## API

```ts
type DynamicTableProps = {
  data: Record<string, unknown>[]
  columns?: ColumnConfig[]
  pageSize?: number
  searchable?: boolean
  sortable?: boolean
  filterable?: boolean
  groupable?: boolean
  toolbarActions?: ReactNode
  rowActions?: (ctx: { row: Record<string, unknown> }) => ReactNode
}
```

- `data` is flattened rows (`toXTableRow`), not rich domain objects
- Map `row.id` back to the domain entity for Edit/Delete handlers
- `toolbarActions` → Create (and similar); `rowActions` → Edit/Delete
- Actions column is automatic when `rowActions` is set; skip group header rows
- Never use key `__actions` in column configs / search fields

## Feature columns file

Export `xTableColumns: ColumnConfig[]` and `toXTableRow(entity)`. Prefer displaying joined names (`departmentName`) over raw UUIDs.

See `.docs/components/tables.md` and list-page CRUD docs for wiring.
